  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 200 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of @salt{}ed water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1} (for 4, zest one lemon and quarter both).

In a #small bowl{}, combine parsley, 3 TBSP @olive oil{3%tbsp} (5 TBSP for 4), a pinch of garlic, a pinch of lemon zest, and lemon juice to taste. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}; set aside.

> Skip boiling water for cauliflower rice!

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary; toss on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Pat @tilapia{11%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; rub each fillet with @olive oil{1%teaspoon}. Season with @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Place on empty side of sheet.

Roast on top rack until green beans are tender and tilapia is cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}. (For 4 servings, divide between 2 sheets; roast green beans on top rack and tilapia on middle rack.)

Meanwhile, once water is boiling, add @Israeli Couscous{2.5%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Drain thoroughly and return to pot.

Add half the @Garlic Herb Butter{2%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings) to pot with couscous; stir until butter is melted and couscous is coated. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat; keep covered until ready to serve.

> Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium pot over medium-high heat. Add cauliflower rice, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and any excess liquid has absorbed, 6-8 minutes. Cook through the rest of this step as instructed.

Heat a #medium dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Sliced Almonds{1/2%ounce} and toast, stirring occasionally, until golden brown, ~{2-4%minutes}. Turn off heat. Transfer to a #cutting board{}; finely chop half the almonds.

Stir chopped almonds into bowl with gremolata. Add a small pinch of @?Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon} if desired. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste.

Divide couscous, green beans, and tilapia between plates. Spoon almond-parsley gremolata over tilapia. Scatter remaining almonds over green beans and top with a pinch of chili flakes if desired. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Tilapia is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.